# Cross-platform line endings — HARD REQUIREMENT (Windows + macOS + Linux).
#
# Shell scripts and Python are executed on Windows via Git Bash / python3. A
# CRLF checkout — the Windows default (core.autocrlf=true) — puts a `\r` on
# every line, which breaks bash (`$'\r': command not found`, broken shebang)
# and can corrupt the engine's scripts. That would break EVERY migration,
# sync_engine.sh, install.sh, and the python pipeline for a friend on Windows.
# So every text file the engine ships is normalised to LF on all platforms.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders for the executable/parsed formats that MUST stay LF.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf
*.yaml  text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf

# PowerShell (if ever added as the Windows-equivalent of a shell path) is the
# one exception — it prefers CRLF.
*.ps1   text eol=crlf
